	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=25399'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<img src='/i/rank_icons/admin.gif' border=0 alt=''> <span style='color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; '>Kytherea</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Community Relations Manager<br>
			
				Posts: 7934<br>
				
				Registered: 04-14-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=25399'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=shadowknightbalance&message.id=5328#M5328">13</a> of 25
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 6772 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;
<P>1.&nbsp; Knight tanking is closer to Beastlords/Rangers/Monks than it is to Warriors.&nbsp; Being a tank class we should be closer to Warriors than to non tanking dps classes. <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&nbsp;<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></P>
<P>2.&nbsp; With the amount mobs cast these days SK's have great difficulty fulfiling their secondary role of pulling.&nbsp; If we could have a chance to not have our feigns broken by spells it would help alot. <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being discussed) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&nbsp;<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></P>
<P>3.&nbsp; SK's need some line of spells which scales to the mob.&nbsp; Paladins have stuns which always reduce x% of the mobs attack time, Warriors have Defensive/Evasive/Stonewall to always reduce x% of the mobs dps, SK's need a tanking ability that scales.&nbsp; <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&nbsp;<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></P>
<P>4.&nbsp; SK's and Paladins are the only melee classes without a form of Parry/Riposte/Dodge disc.&nbsp; We need one for emergencies and tank switches badly. <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&nbsp;<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></P>
<P>5.&nbsp; Rangers recieved offensive/weapon skill caps equal to Warriors as they're an offensive class.&nbsp; Following the same logic knights should recieve ALL defensive skill caps equal to Warriors rather than just the Defense cap equaling Warriors. <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&nbsp;<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></P>
<P>6.&nbsp; To give SK's more group friendliness we would like a necro like res that uses essence emeralds.&nbsp; One of the main strengths of Knights is that they're supposed to offer utility if our utility benefits ourselves only it doesn't sufficently counter the tanking differences between us and Warriors. <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&nbsp;<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></P>
<P>7.&nbsp; Due to most boss mobs being tuned for defensive in raids it puts too large a strain on a guilds requirement of Warriors.&nbsp; Awhile ago Druids were given better heals allowing them to fill in some for Clerics lessening a guilds dependance on that class.&nbsp; The same thing should be done with Knights giving us a defensive-like disc lessening the necessity for a guild to field 6+ Warriors per raid for the bosses. <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&nbsp;<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></P>
<P>8.&nbsp; Mobs swing faster as they get higher level, with GoD we had lots of trouble channeling spells and in Omens mobs continue to hit faster but we recieve no increase to channeling.&nbsp; All hybrids flat out need higher channeling to perform their jobs better.&nbsp; It also makes sense from a game standpoint since it's our job to cast while being hit. <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&nbsp;<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></P>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>9.&nbsp; Aura of Hate is a beneficial spell which is only useful to some clases but cannot be clicked off.&nbsp; This makes the spell line unattractive for many players because the casters/priests in their groups get upset about being buffed with things which are useless to them and cannot be removed.&nbsp; It would help greatly if&nbsp;this could be clicked off.&nbsp; Also, Aura of Pain should be able to be clicked off as well despite being self only. <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></DIV>
<P>10.&nbsp; Our Epic 1.5 (and 2.0 most likely) need some adjustments. <SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000>(all epics currently being re-evaluated)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></P>
<UL>
<LI>The click effects don't scale in line with other classes.&nbsp; The upgrade from 1.5 to 2.0 is a 25% increase of the leechcurse portion and the accuracy recieves a 40% increase.&nbsp; All other epic effects recieve a 50% increase in power except for the SK weapon. 
<LI>The effect doesn't have enough of an impact in its current form.&nbsp; It only provides a couple hundred HP&nbsp;per group member every 10 minutes, casting Zevfeers bite twice helps a group out more.&nbsp; The current power of the effect only justifies a 2 minute recast.&nbsp; The effect should be more along the lines of +10% chance to hit and 33% leechcurse for 1.5 and +15% chance to hit and 50% leechcurse for 2.0. 
<LI>The effect doesn't last long enough.&nbsp; Our effect only lasts for 3 ticks (13-18 seconds).&nbsp; Other classes have 1 minute durations with 10 minute recasts on their effects.&nbsp; Our effect also provides less of a boost than other classes.&nbsp; The durations on our click effects need to be more in line with other classes. 
<LI>There are many advantages to using shields which SK's (and Paladins) miss out on by using their epics.&nbsp; The original epic weapons contained the bonuses which shields provided at the time in them because a shield could not be used with it.&nbsp; We would like to see this happen again on the new epic weapons.&nbsp; These weapons should be Bash enabled, work with the Shield Block AA, and have their AC function like shield AC does.</LI></UL></SPAN></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Kytherea ~~wielding a giant hammer & a hairless War Hamster~~<br><br>"I'm late, I'm late...."
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
