	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=25399'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<img src='/i/rank_icons/admin.gif' border=0 alt=''> <span style='color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; '>Kytherea</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Community Relations Manager<br>
			
				Posts: 7934<br>
				
				Registered: 04-14-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=25399'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=shadowknightbalance&message.id=5783#M5783">17</a> of 25
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 4893 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><SPAN Verdana? FONT-FAMILY: 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE:>&nbsp;
<P>1. Harm Touch: <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)<BR></FONT>-The damage per level of the non AA HT has fallen behind. From levels 1-40 it gave an additional 10 damage per level, from levels 41 to 65 it gave an additional 30 damage per level, and from levels 66 to 70 there is only a 10 damage per level increase. We would like the amount of damage HT gives per level from levels 66+ to be adjusted to something more appropriate such as 50/level or atleast 30/level.</P>
<P>-Improved Harm Touch should refresh on death, it originally did and was changed around the time GoD was released. We feel this change is fair since the Paladin counterpart Improved Lay Hands is capable of refreshing on death</P>
<P>-Paladins recieve two Lay Hands variants through AA's (Hand of Piety and Improved Lay Hands). These AA's are on seperate timers and one won't block the other from working. SK's recieve two HT variants through AA's as well (Improved Harm Touch and Leech Touch) however, these are on the same timer allowing only one to be used every refresh (36-72 min depending on AA's). We feel that it would be appropriate for Improved Harm Touch to be on the same timer as regular Harm Touch with Leech Touch on it's own seperate timer just as the Paladin counterparts to these AA's are. In addition to this Leech Touch should have the same recycle time as Hand of Piety once on seperate timers.</P>
<P>-Improved Harm Touch could use a look at the damage it provides. Since it becomes aviable at level 59 it's base damage remains at 1000 damage and does not increase, infact without AA's to improve its damage this HT is less powerful than the normal one starting at level 61. We would like the damage of IHT to have the same base damage of our regular HT so that it is in all senses an improved Harm Touch.</P>
<P>-Lifetap HT needs the name of it's hotkey changed from Leech Curse to Leech Touch or Life Curse (name of the aa in the aa window or of the spell it casts), our level 60 discipline is called Leechcurse and having multiple abilities sharing the same name can be confusing.</P>
<P>-Our lifetap HT needs to have the ability to be focused with disease damage increasing effects as well as having the capability of being enchanced by our Unholy Aura discipline.</P>
<P>-Improved Harm Touch is rather difficult to get higher end focus effects for. In order to make focus effects for our HT more common we would like Improved Harm Touch changed to magic resist with a massive negative resist modifier such as -1000 or -5000 so that it's still effectively unresistable but has a greater selection of focus. This would allow people far more freedom in choosing gear and not force SK's to carry around old gear to swap in simply for a HT however if done we would also like Unholyaura to not change IHT's resist check to disease if it would.</P>
<P>2. In fights where the content is weaker or the mob has a high DB but low DI a class more focused on avoidence makes a better tank than a class more focused on mitigation. We feel that tank classes should always be able to outtank a non tank class of similar gear regardless of the content. For this reason we would like something such as an innate level of shielding for all 3 tank classes to help on group content such as this. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></P>
<P>3. SK's and Paladins are the only melee classes without a form of Parry/Riposte/Dodge disc. We would like one for emergency situations. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning </FONT></P>
<P>4. Our Terror spells prior to Terror of Discord are inadequete for their job. With some of the proposed changes to spell based aggro and to fear it becomes more important now than before to fix these lower end taunt spells so that they provide decent aggro for SK's who don't have their OoW taunt spells as well as the fact that higher level SK's will be losing a source of non damage aggro and will need to rely on working lower level terrors to ensure we still maintain adequete non damage aggro. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></P>
<P>5. Shadowknight group utility is rather low compared to that of most classes, with the invent of the guild lobby one of our bigger methods of helping people has vanished as people would much rather summon in the lobby than run back for us to summmon. As a result we would like to recieve the Convergence spell to increase our usefulness in some areas where our desireability isn't very high. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></P>
<P>6. Our Aura/Theft lines of spells (Aura of Hate, Aura of Pain, Aura of Darkness, Theft of Hate, Theft of Pain) have recourses which cannot be clicked off. We would like for these buffs to be clickable, in addition to this the group spells (all but the Pain line) should goto the short duration buff box. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></P>
<P>7. A bump from 25% to 30% on Soul Shield with an increase of the rune from 10,000 to 12,000. The reason for this is that in most cases there is no ingame difference between using the 61 and 69 disciplines, in the rare situations where the 61 disc will run out before the 69 disc (situations where dps intake is 800+) debuffs are already in and heals are stabilized resulting in no significant differences between the two abilities as they are currently. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></P>
<P>8. Mobs swing faster as they get higher level, with GoD we had lots of trouble channeling spells and in Omens mobs continue to hit faster but we recieve no increase to channeling. All hybrids flat out need higher channeling to perform their jobs better. It also makes sense from a game standpoint because it's our job to cast while being hit. <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning </FONT></P>
<P>9. We would like to have the same Dodge/Parry/Riposte skillcaps as Warriors <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning </FONT></P>
<P>10. Since the release of GoD the number of caster mobs in zones has gone up tremendously, this is causing many SK's that pull difficulties which slow us down significantly if not in some cases make an SK attempting to FD pull impossible. Many SK's view pulling as their secondary role and would like to be capable in it just as other classes such as Monks enjoy being capable in their two biggest roles of pulling and dps. To help with this we would like a way to help prevent our feigns from being broken by spells.&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being discussed) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning </FONT><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: red?><FONT color=#ff0000></P></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Kytherea ~~wielding a giant hammer & a hairless War Hamster~~<br><br>"I'm late, I'm late...."
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
